    </p>
    @* Search engine optimization (SEO) *@
    <article>
        <h3>
            Search engine optimization (SEO)
        </h3>
        <p>
            This is a technique that aims to improve the ranking of online content on search engines, such as Google or
            Bing, by using keywords, links, and other factors that match the user's search query.
        </p>
    </article>
    @* Search engine marketing (SEM) *@
    <article>
        <h3>
            Search engine marketing (SEM)
        </h3>
        <p>
            This is a technique that involves paying for ads that appear on search engine results pages, such as Google
            Ads or Bing Ads. The ads are triggered by the user's search query and are usually based on a pay-per-click
            (PPC) model
        </p>
    </article>
    @* Content marketing *@
    <article>
        <h3>
            Content marketing
        </h3>
        <p>
            This is a technique that involves creating and distributing valuable, relevant, and engaging content, such
            as blogs, videos, podcasts, eBooks, etc., to attract and retain a target audience. The content is usually
            related to the product or service that the marketer offers and aims to educate, entertain, or inspire the
            audience
        </p>
    </article>
